<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>Spring + React isomorphic templating</title>
    <link href="lib/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet" />
    <link href="style.css" rel="stylesheet" />
</head>

<body>
<nav class="navbar navbar-inverse navbar-fixed-top">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="navbar-header">
            <button type="button" class="navbar-toggle collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#navbar"
                    aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="navbar">
                <span class="sr-only">Toggle navigation</span>
                <span class="icon-bar"></span>
                <span class="icon-bar"></span>
                <span class="icon-bar"></span>
            </button>
            <a class="navbar-brand" href="#">Spring + React isomorphic templating</a>
        </div>
        <div id="navbar"
             class="navbar-collapse collapse"><%= MyApp.renderCommentForm() %></div>
    </div>
</nav>

<div class="jumbotron">
    <div class="container">
        <h3>Spring, Javascript Templating Engine (.ejs), React (.jsx), Server-Sent Events - Isomorphic, very progressively enhanced..</h3>
        <noscript>
            <p style="color: red">You don't have javascript enabled. But no worries, this still works...</p>
        </noscript>
        <p>This Spring + React application uses the same templates on server and client side. Try to disable Javascript
            and see that the application still renders and works perfectly!</p>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="container">
    <div id="comments"
         class="row"><%= MyApp.renderCommentList(comments) %></div>
    <hr />
    <div id="cropper"
         class="row"><%= MyApp.renderCropper("test") %></div>
    <footer>
        <p>&copy; <a href="http://easybird.be" target="_blank">Easybird.be</a></p>
    </footer>
</div>

<script src="lib/js/jquery.min.js"></script>
<script src="lib/js/bootstrap.min.js"></script>
<script src="output/bundle.js"></script>
</body>
</html>